[[File:winterwinds.JPG|200px|thumb|left|A scene in the music video for "Winter Winds".]] The video to accompany the release of "Winter Winds" was released onto [[YouTube]] on 18 November 2009<ref>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_KCg_QEHtkY</ref>. It begins with the quartet running out of a forest covered in party banners and balloons. The video then flickers between the members preparing for a performance of the single in a hay-covered field and the members singing to the song as they stroll down a deserted country road. After reaching the end of the road, the video switches to scenes of the band in the tour caravan as well as the four of them playing in a grassy garden. Other scenes shown in the music video include the band going on stage to perform, the individual members slowly walking away from the camera in the field and images of the members gazing out of the window whilst on a train.
